## 1. Top-level hunt schema

This is the **single JSON object** the runtime loads and the creator dashboard edits.

```jsonc
{
  "id": "great-metaspace-race",
  "title": "The Great MetaSpace Race",
  "description": "A simple treasure hunt through space and time.",
  "difficulty": "standard",          // optional: easy | standard | hard
  "version": 1,                      // schema version
  "settings": {
    "globalTimerSeconds": 0,        // 0 = no global timer
    "maxAttempts": 0,               // 0 = unlimited
    "themeId": "default",           // maps to /themes
    "backgroundImageId": "space_01" // host/admin-chosen background
  },
  "nodes": {
    "start_001": { /* node object */ },
    "portal_001": { /* node object */ },
    "puzzle_001": { /* node object */ }
  },
  "items": {
    "ruby_key": { /* item object */ },
    "silver_token": { /* item object */ }
  },
  "rewards": {
    "reward_001": { /* reward object */ }
  },
  "sponsors": {
    "sponsor_001": { /* sponsor object */ }
  }
}
```

Key points:

- **Hunts are data** (locked philosophy).
- Nodes, items, rewards, sponsors are **separate domains** but live in the same hunt file (or can be split later).

