## 2. Base node contract (all node types)

Every node type must obey this base shape:

```jsonc
{
  "id": "node_001",
  "type": "start",                 // one of the standard node types
  "title": "Start your engines!",
  "body": "It's time to go all in!",
  "sceneId": "scene_001",          // optional grouping
  "next": null,                    // simple next (for linear nodes)
  "choices": [],                   // branching choices (for story/puzzle/etc.)
  "requirements": {
    "items": [],                   // ["ruby_key", "silver_token"]
    "flags": [],                   // ["solved_intro_riddle"]
    "expression": ""               // optional advanced condition string
  },
  "onEnter": {
    "effects": [],                 // effect objects
    "rewardId": null               // reward on enter (optional)
  },
  "onExit": {
    "effects": [],
    "rewardId": null               // reward on exit (optional)
  },
  "timer": {
    "seconds": 0,                  // 0 = no node timer
    "onExpireNodeId": null         // where to go if timer expires
  },
  "failNodeId": null,              // where to go if requirements fail
  "metadata": {}                   // free-form creator/runtime metadata
}
```

This is the **universal contract**. Node types then **extend** this.

